##### I joined [Polywork](https://www.polywork.com/) and as a result found out that they allow you setup a custom domain for your profile which is very helpful for showcase of your timeline ! In this article, I'll share how I did this with a domain pointed in [Cloudflare](https://www.cloudflare.com/).

### At First, What is [Polywork](https://www.polywork.com/)?

Polywork new professional social network to share who you are, what you do and what you want to collaborate on. It is an awesome social platform made for **Multiplayers** - storytellers, creatives, developers, designers, mentors, podcasters, investors and anyone who is looking to build a platform with their personal and professional work and achievements in the form of timeline that allows you to create your identity - who you are, what you care about and what you are capable of.

![](https://www.giftegwuenu.dev/images/uploads/screen-shot-2021-06-07-at-6.54.44-am.png)

Consider it a blend of LinkedIn and Twitter where it's a stage you can share in a real sense anything without feeling like it's not the correct spot for it to be shared. Polywork is as yet in beta right now however if you'll like to join [you can reach out to me](https://www.facebook.com/saugatrimal.pro/) and I'll share an invite code with you.

Let's say you have setup your profile now and want to add a custom domain or subdomain, how would you approach this?

![](data:image/png;base64,)

After getting there scroll a little down and you will get to see

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### **Setting Up Custom Domain**

Select your domain name provider that manages your DNS records or if your provider is not on this list you can send mail to [polywork support](https://mail.google.com/mail/ca/u/0/?fs=1\&tf=cm\&source=mailto\&su=My+domain+provider+is+not+available\&to=support@polywork.com).

Luckily, you can discover a [document that tells you the best way to do this on the settings page](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1SbQr83Bi4-nti1s0f0LYl1iu_Gs2wIOMrouc8\_GHumU/edit) however for my case I was not utilizing Name's yet rather pointed my domain to my Cloudflare account as i am not able to manage my dns setting from [Name's Dashboard](https://name.com/).

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/\_static/app-assets/images/download%20\(2\).png)

So what this meant was I couldn't follow the guide because I can't setup a host record directly on Name.com

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/\_static/app-assets/images/download%20\(1\).png)

In my case, I needed to point **custom DNS** target on my domain which is in Cloudflare . So if this is the same for your case then follow the steps outlined below:

*   Step 1: Go over to your CloudFlare Dashboard, Click on your domain

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/_static/app-assets/images/groovy-elm.png)

*   Step 2: Then, navigate to the DNS Settings

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/_static/app-assets/images/incredible-lime.png)

*   Step 3: Click on the add new record button. Here you can already see mine as I set it up on [timeline.saugatreemal.engineer](https://timeline.saugatreemal.engineer/)

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/_static/app-assets/images/blue-europa.png)

*   Step 4: Now, add the details for your custom domain here you can choose the CNAME record type and add the name you want to use as subdomain, I used timeline but you can use anything you want and lastly, go over to your Polywork settings page and copy the **Heroku domain** you have there, set proxies status to DNS only and set the TTL to 5 min.

![](https://preview--ultra-lavender-057be.stackbit.dev/_static/app-assets/images/nervous-mars.png)

That's all you need to do, save this and wait for at least 24 hours to allow the Heroku domain map to your newly setup sub-domain and you should have it all working when next you visit you new sub-domain!

I hope you found this helpful!![](https://github.com/saugat-rimal/blog.saugatrimal.engineer/blob/e1a6b355a00a060ec5aa605efb80739273274aeb/public/images/click%20to%20domain.png)
